wikipedia_page.main: Henry Charles Cadogan, 4th Earl Cadogan PC (15 February 1812 – 8 June 1873), styled Viscount Chelsea between 1820 and 1864,  was a British diplomat and Conservative politician. He served as Captain of the Yeomen of the Guard between 1866 and 1868.

response: Cadogan was the eldest son of Henry Cadogan, 4th Earl Cadogan, by his wife Mary, daughter of Reverend Gerald Wellesley, younger brother of Arthur Wellesley, 1st Duke of Wellington. He was born in the city of Durham and baptised at St James's, Westminster, London. He was educated at Eton College and Christ Church, Oxford.States he was born at "Durham College".
*Henry Cadogan, 4th Earl Cadogan (1812–1873), styled Viscount Chelsea between 1820 and 1864, British diplomat and politician
